# Growlog Docs And ADRs

- Preserve ADR intent when editing docs. If implementation diverges, document the new decision instead of silently drifting.
- Keep terminology consistent with the canonical model in ADR-002 and the retrieval or trust language from ADR-003 and ADR-004.
- When documenting AI behavior, separate facts, interpretation, hypotheses, recommendations, missing data, and confidence.
- When documenting SOP, report, or photo flows, describe deterministic stages and ownership boundaries.
- Do not document public-access patterns that bypass RLS, tenant isolation, or sanitization.
